      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MEG'S MAGIC (2) resumes and boasts a solid fresh record. Was flashing home without winning in tougher races last campaign and the form around her reads favourably. Has jumped out well in readiness and is expected to make a bright return. MAGIC ISLAND (3) showed her usual tactical speed when resuming at headquarters but was only run down late. Better for that and gets 2kgs off with the claimer engaged. Will prove tough to run down if left alone through the middle stages. ZENACITY (4) is often her own worst enemy as she continues to leave herself with too much ground to bridge but has been flashing late. Holder sticks from last time which is a good push. LAPILLI (1) speared across to lead when resuming in town earlier this month but struggled to go on with it in the lane. Fitter and will find this a fair bit easier. Can improve significantly. SHALHAVMUSIK (5) was well below her best when resuming but should improve with that run under her belt and is a second-up winner.",
